To strengthen our fast-growing operations in our office in Stockholm, we are looking for a new colleague with a proactive mindset and strong analytical skills to join our team as a
 **Business Analyst** 
 .










 When working at Main you will be surrounded by a dynamic, fast-growing and international work environment. You will join a dedicated team of proactive, like-minded professionals and work together to achieve common goals. You will have the opportunity to develop your skills and grow professionally.










 As a member of the investment team, you will actively be involved in evaluating investment opportunities and deal execution. Supporting the investment management team within one of the top performing PE firms.










**Why you would love to work for us:** 



* You will work in a fun, young and dedicated team within an informal open corporate culture;
* You will gain a lot of knowledge and insight in a leading sector focused investment fund;
* You will get the possibility to take part in our international exchange program with our offices in The Hague or Düsseldorf;
* You will get a lot of responsibilities at an early stage;
* You will get a competitive salary with a steep growth curve in career path;
* You will get an education with a combination of individual trainings, learning from the job and educational modules;
* You will get to take part in our generous pension scheme;
* You will get to enjoy our Company Wellness Allowance.









**Why you would be a great fit for us:** 



* You have or are close to getting an Academic Master in Business or Economics.
* You have 0-3 years of relevant professional experience (including internships) within the PE/M&A sector, preferably in IT.
* You have good analytical skills and knowledge of financial and management accounting;
* You have affinity with Software/IT companies or would like to learn all about them.
* You are a real team player who is dedicated and hardworking but also knows how to have fun;
* You have the ability to work independently and set priorities in changing and exciting work environment;
* You have good communication and social skills and have an excellent command of English and other Nordic language (Danish, Norwegian, Finnish or Swedish) in word and writing.









**What your responsibilities will be:** 



* You will be involved in the entire investment process as an active part of the investment team;
* You will proactively contact and engage with potential dealflow, as well as portfolio companies;
* You will assist portfolio companies with strategic developments and perform performance excellence projects within our portfolio companies;
* You will analyze company and market information, establish financial models and provide insight into investment and financing proposals;
* You will prepare Investment Proposals; help preparing the Quarterly Reporting and organizing events;
* You will assist (Sr.) Investment Managers and Partners in daily activities and assist portfolio companies with strategic developments.

The Company:









 Meet Unit4. We’re in business for people.








 We’re a fast-paced growth SaaS company, changing the game in people focused solutions for mid-market people-centric organisations. Our solutions supportsour customers in delivering an exceptional people experience to their customers - from boosting success for students and professionals, to empowering the public servants and non-profit teams doing good in the world.








 For people-centric organizations, Unit4 offers not just a better place to work, but a better way to work. We transform work to be more meaningful and inspiring through software that’s self-driving, adaptive and intuitive, intelligently automating administrative tasks and providing easy access to the answers people need.








 Our solutions all arise from a simple premise: give people the means to focus on what matters, and the people they serve will benefit.








 Read more on our website about how we transform work and how people feel about it, so our customers and their people can thrive.








 At Unit4 you’ll have the opportunity to work within a challenging, fast paced international environment. We’ll invest in your personal and professional growth and we don’t focus on how many days you work, we trust you to deliver results, that’s why we provide an uncapped time off policy! Join us if you would like to be part of something special; helping shape a global people-centric cloud company.











**Job Description**

 Job Description








 As Senior Legal Counsel for the Nordics you will provide broad legal advice and assistance to the business in Sweden, Norway, Finland and Denmark and will work together in project teams with legal colleagues across the world.








 As Senior Legal Counsel you will be responsible for negotiating, drafting and reviewing a broad range of commercial SaaS software agreements, service and support agreements, government tenders, NDA’s, LOI’s and similar. Furthermore, you may assist the Unit4 Nordics operations with day to day legal advise on corporate, HR and finance matters.








 You will work closely together with your colleagues in the legal department. As part of the global legal team, you will enhance legal awareness in the business, by providing training and advising management on relevant legal development that could affect our business.








 You will be part of growing legal team of 12+, reporting directly to the Assistant General Counsel.











**Qualifications**

**Education**




 Swedish Law Degree (preferably masters level) (IP law, Economic law or Business law)








**Knowledge and Skills**



* Strong project management skills;
* Excellent presentation skills in both informal and formal situations;
* Excellent written and oral communication skills in English and Swedish.
* Good interpersonal skills and relationship management skills;
* Self-starter so therefore also a quick learner;
* Team player;
* Ability to work collaboratively with senior staff in management and other disciplines;
* Committed to excellent performance and a practical understanding of how to deliver results;
* Be hands on and have a Can Do mentality;
* Energetic individual with unusual initiative;
* Ability to work under pressure and be flexible;
* Strong work ethic and enthusiastic about new challenges;
* Creative thinker and resourceful problem solver.



**Experience**



* A minimum of 5 years post qualified experience;
* Significant experience working in house with sales teams and closing SaaS contracts for both private and public sector customers;
* Experience in private law firm combined with experience as in house counsel in a technology business;
* Up to date knowledge on data protection and privacy regulations;
* IT savvy.



